Why New Names Change Fields

When a useful name appears, three things happen.

1. Attention locks onto the pattern

Before the name, the pattern is invisible.

After the name, it becomes obvious everywhere.

Example:

Once people understood feedback loops, they started seeing them in:
	•	ecosystems
	•	economics
	•	psychology
	•	engineering

⸻

2. Knowledge becomes transferable

The pattern can be applied across domains.

Example:

Network theory now explains:
	•	social groups
	•	neurons
	•	disease spread
	•	power grids

⸻

3. Thinking becomes faster

Instead of explaining the pattern each time, people say the name.

Language becomes cognitive infrastructure.

